# No backend configuration required — campaign state syncs peer-to-peer via
# WebRTC (crdtbus) and persists locally in the browser (IndexedDB).
#
# Peers find each other through a PeerJS signaling server. The default is
# drpeer.onrender.com — the self-hosted PeerServer used by druthers, the
# crdtbus reference app. It runs on Render's free tier, so the first
# connection after an idle spell can take ~10-50s while it cold-starts
# (gameplay is local-first and unaffected; sync just starts late). Point this
# at your own peerjs-server deployment, or the public cloud (0.peerjs.com),
# if you prefer (hostname only, HTTPS assumed):
#
# VITE_PEERJS_HOST=drpeer.onrender.com
#
# When both peers are behind symmetric NAT / carrier-grade NAT, WebRTC needs
# a TURN relay. Short-lived TURN credentials are fetched (POST, response
# shape { iceServers: [...] }) from this endpoint before connecting; failures
# fall back gracefully to PeerJS's default STUN servers. Set it to your own
# credential endpoint, or to an empty string to disable the fetch:
#
# VITE_TURN_URL=https://turn-worker.gavmor.workers.dev/api/turn
